In a #small pot{}, combine @Israeli couscous{2.5%ounce}, @chicken stock concentrate{2}, and 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings). Bring to a boil over medium-high heat. Once boiling, cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until couscous is tender, ~{6-8%minutes}. Drain any excess water if necessary.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While couscous cooks, wash and dry produce.

Trim and halve @zucchini{1}(trimmed) lengthwise; cut crosswise into ½-inch-thick half-moons. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed), separating whites from greens. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon} in a large #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add zucchini and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring frequently, until browned and tender, ~{4-7%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a plate and cover with #foil{} to keep warm. Wipe out pan.

While zucchini cooks, open package of @chopped chicken breast{10%ounce} and drain off any excess liquid.

Place chicken in a large #bowl{}; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add @cornstarch{1%tablespoon} and toss until chicken is fully coated.

Heat a drizzle of cooking oil in pan used for zucchini over medium-high heat. Add coated chicken and cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Reduce heat under pan with chicken to medium. Add another drizzle of cooking oil, scallion whites, garlic, salt, and pepper. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add @hot honey{2%teaspoon} and @butter{1%tablespoon}; cook, stirring constantly, until sauce is glossy and chicken is thoroughly coated.

Fluff couscous with a #fork{}; taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Divide couscous between shallow #bowls{}. Top with chicken and zucchini in separate sections. Garnish with scallion greens and as many @chili flakes{1%teaspoon} as you like. Serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.